      "description": "This 2008 Chevrolet Corvette Z06 is a purist's performance machine, powered by the hand-built LS7 7.0L V8 featuring titanium connecting rods and a dry-sump lubrication system for consistent oil pressure under high lateral G-loads. The drivetrain is anchored by a rear-mounted Tremec TR-6060 six-speed manual transaxle and a limited-slip differential, ensuring optimal weight distribution. The hydroformed aluminum chassis remains rigid, complemented by a factory-tuned suspension with monotube dampers and large-diameter stabilizer bars. Stopping power is provided by six-piston front and four-piston rear calipers over cross-drilled rotors. This vehicle is mechanically sound with a crisp throttle response and precise gear synchronization. While showing minor cosmetic wear consistent with its 'good' status, the structural and performance components remain in excellent working order.",
